notesStmt.note: This Ottoman manuscript is a gloss (ḥāshiyah) by Kemalpaşazade (d. 940 AH / 1533 CE) on the commentary on the Qur’an composed by ʿAbd Allāh al-Bayḍawī (d. ca. 685 AH / 1286 CE) entitled Anwār al-tanzīl. Transcribed in 966 AH / 1558 CE, the present copy was made from the author's holograph by ʿUthmān ibn Manṣūr. The text is written in Turkish nastaʿlīq script in black ink with the words qāla and aqūlu in red, and it opens with an illuminated incipit with titlepiece inscribed with the doxological formula (basmalah). The dark brown leather binding has a central lobed oval with pendants and cornerpieces with arabesque designs on a gold ground.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Arabic.

msItem.incipit: قال اما العظملة اقول حقيقلة او ادعاء ...
msItem.note: Colophon (fol. 151a) is followed by what appears to be additional glosses beginning with the first chapter (Sūrat fātiḥat al-kitāb) (fol. 152a); text ends abruptly on fol. 156a; numerous marginal glosses known as minhiyāt present, attributable to Ibn Kamāl Pāshā

colophon.note: al-ḥamd li-man yasurru lanā al-farāgh ʿan al-taḥrīr wa-al-al-tanmīq ʿan nuskhat al-muṣ [al-muṣannif] bi-khaṭṭih al-sharīf /1/ ṣāḥib al-taḥqīq wa-al- tadqīq [placed in the left margin: al-shahīr bi-al-faḍl wa-al-kamāl // Aḥmad ibn Sylaymān ibn Kamāl // al-mustakhraj ʿan baḥr al-ʿulūm bāshan? // al-maʿrūf bayna al-anām bi-Ibn Kamāl Pāshā //] ʿalá yad al-faqīr ilá al-irshād wa-al-tawfīq /2/ al-rājī ʿan rabbih al-hidāyah ilá sawāʾ al-ṭarīqqʾilan fī duʿāʾih al-malik /3/ al-karīm yā walī al-rushd yā hādī bi-Qurʾān ḥakīm ihdi ʿUthmān ibn Manṣūr /4/ al-ṣirāṭ al-mustaqīm fī laylat yawm al-khamīs thālith shahr Dhī al-Ḥijjah /5/ li-sanat sitt wa-sittīn wa-tisʿimi<ʾ>ah min al-hijrah al-nabawīyah sanah 966 /6/
Written in red ink, giving details about the model (exemplar), the author's name, the name of the scribe, and the date of copying

p.catchwords: No isolated catchwords; last word on the bottom line of versos repeated at the beginning of rectos

handDesc.handNote: Written in Turkish nastaʿlīq script in black ink with the words qāla and aqūlu in red

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated incipit with titlepiece with the doxological formula (basmalah) in tawqīʿ script (fol. 1b); fols. 1b-2b and 7a-b with gold framing lines around text

decoNote.title: Binding
decoNote.note: This dark brown leather binding with damaged, backwards flap has a central lobed oval with pendants and cornerpieces with arabesque designs on a gold ground. The doublures of red leather have a central geometric design.

decoNote.title: Page with stamp and shelf mark
decoNote.note: This page bears the bequest (waqf) seal of the Vizier al-Shahīd ʿAlī Pāshā, dated 1130 AH / 1717 CE, beneath which is the original shelf mark 191.

decoNote.title: Illuminated incipit page with titlepiece
decoNote.note: This illuminated incipit page has a titlepiece with the doxological formula (basmalah) written in white tawqīʿ script on a gold background.

decoNote.title: Text page with the seal of the Vizier al-Shahīd ʿAlī Pāshā
decoNote.note: At the left of this text page is the bequest (waqf) seal of the Vizier al-Shahīd ʿAlī Pāshā, dated 1130 AH / 1717 CE.

decoNote.title: Colophon
decoNote.note: Written in red ink, this colophon gives details about the model (exemplar), the author's name, the name of the scribe, and the date of copying.

binding.p: Dark brown leather (with damaged flap attached backwards); central lobed oval, pendants, and cornerpieces with arabesque designs on a gold ground; doublures of red leather with a central geometric design

history.provenance: Bequest (waqf) seal of the Vizier al-Shahīd ʿAlī Pāshā, dated 1130 AH, and the original shelf mark 191 beneath (fol. 1a); the same seal impression appears on fols. 1b, 2a, and 156b
